LvXhaijN,Ranked Wars - A Rudimentary Guide,luvariox,CSS,Tuesday 16th of May 2023 03:36:03 PM CDT,"Ranked wars are a ""Tug of War"" style fight, where each team attacks the members of their opponent to gain ""score"", with the ultimate goal of crossing a target net score first. This net target score gets based on the rank and member counts of the factions competing.
If either faction failed to achieve the net target score within 24 hours, it will decrease by 1% of it's original value per hour.

Ranked war score is equivalent to the respect earned on each hit from attacking members of the opponent faction. Which means mugging opponent will bring only 75% of the score that leaving & hospitalizing would.
After the war each participating faction will earn bonus respect, points and caches. Some factors that determine rewards -
[b]Factions rank[/b] [b]-[/b] Higher tier RW ranked factions will receive better rewards.
[b]Number of Members - [/b]More members in a faction will increase the rewards.
[b]Participation -[/b] More participation from members will yield better rewards, either or not we win. Lack of participation, may even be penalized with an additional division loss upon losing.
[b]Underdog - [/b]If an underdog (the faction which is expected to loose ) manages to win they will receive better rewards.
[b]Streak -[/b] A win after a losing streak will provide greater rewards.
[color=#4263eb][size=16][b]Basic Tactics In Order To Win A Ranked War -[/b][/size][/color]
[ul][li][b][color=#1769b5]Hospitalize online / very high battle stat players[/color][/b]
This will help to increase their medical & revive cooldown faster and in turn they won't be able to hit us back for a while.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Leave offline / very low battle stat players[/color][/b]
This will allow us to keep hitting their lower end after a very short period of hospital time, which in turn will help get more respect, lengthen the chain and land bonus chain hits.[/li]

Chaining during a ranked war is absolutely essential. We must build up the respect multiplier in order to maximize our respect gained. We'll have to keep the chain going even if that means occasional hits outside the opponent faction.[/li]
While chaining, we'll have to make sure each and every chain hit is done upon the opponent faction. It'll help us secure large chunks of chain bonus in one go.[/li]
As you've guessed the opponent will also be chaining for that respect multiplier and try to land the bonus hits on us.[/li]

If you are out of energy, going afk, going away for the night or not participating in the war always make sure to be stay hospitalized with your revives turned off. This will prevent the opponent from being able to hit you or land any bonus hits on you. You can use wrong blood bags for short hospitalization (around 1h), For long durations you can use SED's or ask someone to hospitalize you, preferably with merits in Hospitalizing for longer duration. Having someone set a bounty on you may also help.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Always try to get high Fair Fight(FF) bonus[/color][/b]

The fair fight (FF) multiplier ranges between 1x and 3x and is applied for attacking a target with battle stats that are similar to your own. Attacking someone with roughly 75% of your total battle stats or higher yields a FF of 3x. If possible always try to hit people who'll provide higher FF bonus, you can leave those who'll provide lower FF bonus for the lower battle stat people in your faction.[/li]

A retaliation hit is an attack (hospitalization only) made on someone that has attacked one of your faction members within the last 5 minutes. Retaliations provide a multiplier of 1.5x, and can only be claimed once on a player until they attack your faction again. If possible, always try to go for a retal hit than normal ones for the 1.5x bonus.[/li]

The Small Explosive Device method to self-hospitalize is the only time to do this. Reason - many factions have pranksters/tacticians in them, and there is nothing better for them watching you lose 1000 energy, because you opened a parcel with a Horses Head in it. Horses Heads are classed as ""special items"" so this means when you put them in a box and you get to choose the item description. It's common for them to be classed as FHCs / Boosters/ medical Items, with a message that's say, use this to beat the faction etc. The simpler scams are people will dare or try and bully you into opening them. Ignore any parcels receive shortly before or during a war.[/li]
[color=#4263eb][size=16][b]Preparations Before The Start Of A Ranked War - [/b][/size][/color]

It is very important to have your revive settings set to ""No One"". Only set it to ""Everyone"" right before you require a revive and turn it off immediately afterwards. The reason being, you don't want the opponent to hostile revive you and farm respect from you.[/li]

We would want to start stacking energy a bit early, in order to make sure a possible OD doesn't set us back for the war. And make sure to rehab after fully stacking to make sure you don't get hit with Battle Stats Debuff during the war.
We would recommend starting to stack before at least 48 hours or more, in case of an OD we'll still be able to start the war without a lot drug cooldown.[/li]

Make sure that you have full Medical & Booster cooldown available before the war starts. You will need to use a lot of blood bags or other medical items in order to stay out of the hospital, you may need to use FHC/cans to keep the chain alive during the war. Having full cooldowns available helps to give your all.[/li]

It's possible to create up to three loadouts. It's a great addition if you plan on using different weapons/armors/temps or different Mods/ammo on weapons. You can arrange them before the war and swiftly change your loadout during the war.[/li]

Before the RW a list of battle stat spies on the opponent will be provided to everyone. The spies will also get added to torn stats, so if you are using torntools you should be able to check stat spy on their profile during the war. You also need to ensure your Torn Tools Browser extension is connected to Torn Stats via the same API or connect them from ""external services"" in torn tools preferences. Try to pick out targets with at least 75% of your total battle stats in order to maximize on the Fair Fight(FF) bonus. You can easily check how much FF bonus you'll get by going to ""Faction Spies"" in Torn stats, and searching by the faction name and sorting by FF bonus.[img]https://i.imgur.com/3PpILZ8.jpg[/img]You can save choose and save targets in YATA for faster execution during the war and export the yata targets imported in TornPDA.[/li]

The [url=https://greasyfork.org/en/scripts/406516-central-hospital-revive-request]Revive Me script[/url] will help to quickly ask for revives during the war and also toggle between revive setting in the hospital window. [url=https://greasyfork.org/en/scripts/381435-chain-watcher]Chain watcher script[/url] is highly recommended as if set properly it gives a sound warning when the chain timer goes low, helps immensely to keep the chain going.[/li]
It can get really hectic during a war, and you may not get the time to buy required temporary or medical items. It's better to buy those that you may need beforehand.[/li]

If you don't Overdose during the stacking period and able to have no drug cooldown before the war starts, you should take a vicodin 3 hours before the war starts. Vicodin will give you 25% increased battle stats for 4-6 hours, and the great thing is vicodin OD only decreases 150 happiness.[/li]
You may use anything you want as long as it helps you win a fight. However, these are some recommendations -
[color=#1098ad]Combat Helmet[/color]   + good armor rating    - doesn't protect against pepper spray, Choose if you don't train dexterity
[color=#1098ad]Motorcycle Helmet[/color]   - worse armor rating that Combat Helmet    + protects against pepper spray, Choose if you train dexterity
[color=#1098ad]Flexible Body Armor[/color] + great armor rating    - doesn't protect the neck
[color=#1098ad]Full Body Armor[/color]+/- good armor rating, but less than Flexible    + affordable and lots of them in the armory    + protects the [i]neck[/i]
[color=#1098ad]Macana[/color] + more accurate than DBK    - less damage than DBK    Pick if your strength is higher than your speed
[color=#1098ad]Diamond Bladed Knife[/color]    + more damage than macana    - less accurate than macana    Pick if your speed is higher than your strength
[color=#1098ad]ArmaLite[/color]   + more damage than both melee options    + can use mods and special ammo    - less accurate than both melee options
[color=#1098ad]Blowgun[/color]+ deals DOT with poison    + if poison triggers it will deal a lot of damage    - poison doesn't always trigger[/li]

Much like Weapons/Armors it comes down to your preference and playing style. In case you are not sure, please check the [url=https://www.torn.com/forums.php#/p=threads&f=61&t=16252083&b=0&a=0&to=21979427:~:text=needed%20to%20war.-,Attack%20settings,-(It%E2%80%99s%20probably%20worth]Attack Settings[/url] shown in this guide.[/li]

Go with what you've read so far. Attack people for the best FF bonus you can get, try to hit for retals, keep the chain alive at all cost. Leave offline opponents on the street and hospitalize online opponents. The goal is to max the medical cooldown of the online members, and farm respect from the offline members. Also make sure to always land bonus chain hits on our opponent.[/li]

If you are not able to be around during the start of the war or during, you should always stay in the hospital and make sure the opponent cannot farm you for respect. There are a few ways you can accomplish this
1. [color=#f76707]Nasty Surprise in the post (5hrs) -[/color] You buy a Small Explosive Device, but it in a box, then open it. simple, effective, but costs a fair bit.

2. [color=#f76707]Fail a crime -[/color] you can get some seriously long hospital times 8-9+hrs, but it usually comes at the cost of Crime Experience and you would absolutely need a revive to get out, it would wreck your medical cooldown otherwise.

3. [color=#f76707]Use an incorrect blood bag (1hr) -[/color] this is great for those times when you are only able to use natural energy. You let the energy build up, attack a couple of people and then drop yourself in hospital by using the wrong blood bag. Assuming your then offline for longer than 30mins, you haven't wasted any medical cooldown, and can repeat the process again
4. [color=#f76707]Outside hit -[/color] depending on the person who hits you, you can end up in hospital with between 4-6hrs. (depending on perks)[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Be aware of discord pings, in game mails & faction chat[/color][/b]
Leadership will use these methods to convey the latest strategy we'll be using. And we'll also need to communicate to make sure bonus chain hits are used on the opponent.[/li]

During a war chain watching becomes imperative for everyone. We have to make sure the chain doesn't drop at all costs. Specially during Night/Morning (TCT) there are few members around. Try to keep some energy saved in case you need to quickly get a revive/med out to make a hit in order to save the chain. Using multiple tabs for quick attacks are recommended as you might get attacked the moment you are out of the hospital. If you are unable to hit anyone from the opponent then make an outside hit on a target of your choice, we have to keep the chain going.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Turtling to keep the respect bleed in check[/color][/b]

This can happen when most of our faction members (heavy hitters) are away/asleep. The goal is to stay in the hospital or overseas and not let the opponent hit you. Of course all the while we still have to keep the chain alive.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Using Pushes to break a standstill / chain[/color][/b]

Leadership may organize a push for certain situations. It'll mostly happen when either we are stuck in hospital and opponent is not allowing us to come out, or when we are trying to break the opponent's chain by taking advantage of their low activity.

In both cases, Leadership will send newsletter / ping in discord with the time for the push. You need to pick a few targets you can attack and open separate tabs for them in order to quickly hit. When the selected time come we will med out / get revived and attack the pre-determined targets, prioritizing the online targets then idle/offline. The goal is to put the entire enemy faction in the hospital and turn the tide of war.[/li]

This doesn't happen often, but there might be a time when such is organized. Leadership or committee will probably be ones to organize this. A group of people can fairly easily take out a much higher battle stat member by spamming temps and taking advantage of the distraction bonus.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]Low Battle stat/unable to successfully hit anyone[/color][/b]
In case you are in a position where you are unable to hit anyone because of battle stats differences, don't be discouraged, you can still help out a lot during the war ny doing these -
[color=#f76707]1.[/color] Turn off revives and self hospitalize, don't let the enemy farm you for respect or land a bonus hit.

[color=#f76707]2.[/color] Watch the chain and do outside hits on targets of your preference in order to grow the chain or save it. Just make sure not to hit during bonuses as we would need to land all bonus hit on the opponent.
[color=#f76707]3.[/color] If needed, you can assist higher battle stat members by joining their fight and throwing temps and providing a distraction bonus.[/li]
[li][b][color=#1769b5]If you are not participating in the war for a valid reason[/color][/b]

If you are unable to perticipate in the war for any valid resons, you should always either self-hospitalize or travel long distance. You need to make sure you do not get farmed by our opponent for the duration of the war. If perhaps, you are able to make last minute chain saving hits while being overseas than you're already doing a lot.
Long distance flights - South Africa, UAE, China & Japan.[/li]
The threads mentioned below can help a lot to fight, organize and to buy equipment's.
[li][url=https://www.torn.com/forums.php#/p=threads&f=67&t=16259594&b=0&a=0]BS Spies on Walls / RW / Member List[/url][/li]

[/ul]Needless to say this is a very basic guide to ranked wars. Some things have been left out or some of the topics only been touched a bit. The objective of this guide was to give a basic idea of how ranked war works and what do we have to do in order to have a positive winning chance. For any further queries, please do not hesitate to ask.
